---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ReadingProgressBar from '../../components/ReadingProgressBar.astro';
import TableOfContents from '../../components/TableOfContents.astro';
import StocksTable from '../../components/widgets/StocksTable.astro';
import edgeComputingData from '../../components/widgets/edge_computing.json';

const title = "Non-Obvious Edge Computing Stocks";
const description = "Analysis of the infrastructure required to move AI from the cloud to the physical world, focusing on ruggedized networking and on-device inference.";
const pubDate = "May 26, 2026";
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
  <style>
    .article-container {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 3rem;
      max-width: 1300px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      position: relative;
    }
    @media (max-width: 1280px) {
      .article-container {
        display: block;
      }
    }
    .wrap {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 1.25rem 5rem;
      width: 100%;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    .article-header {
      padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem;
      border-bottom: 3px solid var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    .article-header .meta {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      color: rgb(var(--gray));
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    }
    .article-header h1 {
      font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 4.5vw, 2.9rem);
      margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      line-height: 1.15;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: rgb(var(--black));
    }
    .article-header .intro {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
      margin: 0;
    }

    .prose {
      max-width: var(--width-prose);
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
      color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
    }

    .prose p {
      margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .prose h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      color: rgb(var(--black));
      margin: 2.5rem 0 1.25rem;
      line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .prose h3 {
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      color: rgb(var(--black));
      margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
      line-height: 1.25;
    }

    .prose hr {
      border: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
      margin: 3rem 0;
    }

    .prose ul, .prose ol {
      margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }
    .prose li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .callout-box {
      background-color: #FAF9F6;
      border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
      padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem;
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    }
    .callout-box h2 {
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      color: var(--accent-dark);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      border: none;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .callout-box p {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <ReadingProgressBar />
  <Header />
  <main>
    <div class="article-container">
      <div class="wrap">
        
        <header class="article-header">
          <p class="meta">{pubDate} &nbsp;|&nbsp; Tech & AI Hardware</p>
          <h1>{title}</h1>
          <p class="intro">{description}</p>
        </header>

        <section class="prose">
          <p>
            This report focuses on the infrastructure required to move AI from the cloud to the physical world. The research identifies key winners in ruggedized networking, mission-critical machine-to-machine connectivity, and on-device AI inference, specifically neural processing units. The evaluation favors companies solving physical-world constraints, such as vibration, temperature, and power efficiency.
          </p>

          <div class="callout-box">
            <h2>Screening Note</h2>
            <p>
              The table is a reference surface for comparing edge-computing exposure. Sort by ticker, vertical segment, or aggregate score to see how the physical-world constraints cluster.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Reusable Interactive Table Widget -->
          <StocksTable data={edgeComputingData} tableId="edgeComputingTable" />

          <hr />

          <h2>Screener Rules and Methodology</h2>
          <p>
            To isolate high-conviction opportunities in edge computing, our screening model applies three core criteria:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Physical Resilience:</strong> We favor hardware designed to withstand field deployments, focusing on resistance to extreme heat, vibration, and electromagnetic noise.</li>
            <li><strong>Edge Autonomy:</strong> We prioritize on-device inference capabilities over cloud-dependent wrappers, emphasizing localized processing efficiency.</li>
            <li><strong>Valuation Discipline:</strong> We aggressively penalize firms where negative earnings or excessive PEG ratios create an unfavorable risk-reward profile.</li>
          </ul>

          <hr />

          <h2>Top 3 Highest-Conviction Edge Computing Picks (Audited)</h2>
          <p>
            Based on our strict filtering logic and valuation audit, the following three companies represent the strongest opportunities:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Belden Inc. (BDC):</strong> The most disciplined entry in industrial networking. Hardened switches and wiring components represent the non-obvious data backbone of modern factory floors.</li>
            <li><strong>Digi International (DGII):</strong> A high-conviction connectivity play where aggressive growth offsets a rich nominal PE. It remains essential for unbreakable remote M2M links.</li>
            <li><strong>SiTime (SITM):</strong> Holds a dominant position in silicon MEMS timing, serving as a precision timing chokepoint. It remains a high-risk speculative play due to negative trailing earnings.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

      </div>
      <TableOfContents />
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>
